
Scenarios: 

a.	A member attempts to borrow a book with an expired membership.
o Outcome: borrowing fails
o	Scenario is the membership card expiring due to the passage of time. Note, member had not renewed membership before the card expiration date.
o	This is handled by renewing the members membership. BorrowingService must check membership status before approving borrow.

b.	A member returns a book which is damaged.
o	Outcome: book is returned, and member is issued small fine.
o	Scenario is the member returns a visibly damaged book that must be replaced.
o	BorrowingService processes the return but flags the book as damaged; and the library orders a new copy.

c.	Member attempts to exceed the borrowing limit of three books.
o	Ex. borrowing a 4th  book, when the member has already borrowed the limit of 3.
o	Outcome: borrowing fails
o	BorrowingService enforces the borrowing limit. Member class checks and maintains the list of borrowed books.
